<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Item 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	General
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	IKONICS Corporation (&#x201C;IKONICS&#x201D; or the &#x201C;Company&#x201D;) was incorporated in Minnesota as Chroma-Glo,&nbsp;Inc. in 1952 and changed its name to The Chromaline Corporation in 1982.&nbsp; In December&nbsp;2002, the Company changed its name to IKONICS Corporation.&nbsp; The Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	traditional businesses, Domestic,&nbsp;IKONICS Imaging and Export, have been the development, manufacture and selling of photosensitive liquids (&#x201C;emulsions&#x201D;) and films for the screen printing and awards and recognition industries.&nbsp;&nbsp;These sales have been augmented with inkjet receptive films, ancillary chemicals and related equipment to provide a full line of products and services to its customers. These products are sold worldwide primarily through distributors.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2006, the Company began a major effort to diversify and expand its business to industrial markets. These efforts now include the Company&#x2019;s Advanced Material Solutions (&#x201C;AMS&#x201D;) business unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	which uses the Company&#x2019;s proprietary processes and photoresist film for the abrasive etching of composite materials, industrial ceramics, silicon wafers,&nbsp;and glass wafers.&nbsp;&nbsp;The customer base for AMS is primarily the aerospace and electronics industries.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on its expertise in ultraviolet curable fluids and inkjet receptive substrates, the Company has also developed a patented digital texturing technology (&#x201C;DTX&#x201D;) for putting patterns and textures into steel molds for the plastic injection molding industry. The ultimate original equipment manufacturer (&#x201C;OEM&#x201D;) for the Company&#x2019;s DTX technology is primarily the automotive industry. The Company offers a suite of products to the mold making industry.&nbsp;&nbsp;Industrial inkjet printers, which are integral to the DTX system, are manufactured and sold by a strategic partner.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s business plan is to sell consumable fluids and transfer films.&nbsp;&nbsp;For most markets
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	these sales are direct to the mold maker.&nbsp;&nbsp;The DTX technology is being expanded to prototyping where the Company&#x2019;s technology offers a unique combination of high definition, large format prints, and abrasion resistance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Products
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company has four primary technology platforms: Ultraviolet (UV) chemistry, film coating and construction, technical abrasive etching, and industrial inkjet printing. The Company&#x2019;s traditional products and new initiatives are based on these platforms and their combinations. The Company&#x2019;s Chromaline branded products for the screen printing industry and I
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	KONICS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Imaging products for the awards and recognition market are based on UV chemistry and film coating and construction capabilities; the AMS offering is a combination of UV chemistry, film coating and construction and technical abrasive etching capabilities; DTX is a combination of UV chemistry, film coating and construction, and industrial inkjet printing.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is overlap and synergy in the market between the Domestic,&nbsp;Ikonics Imaging, AMS and DTX product offerings, and the Company offers ancillary products, including equipment to provide customers with a total solution.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company considers this combination of core technologies and product offerings to be unique.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Distribution
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	and Customers
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company currently has approximately 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	domestic and international distributors for its Chromaline and ImageMate screen printing emulsions and films.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s abrasive etching products are mainly sold directly to end users in the awards and recognition market under the Ikonics Imaging brand. AMS products are sold either directly to users or the Company offers AMS as a service. DTX includes the sales of consumable inks and films to customers that have purchased specialized industrial inkjet printers from the Company&#x2019;s strategic partner. DTX sales are both direct to users and through distributors. The Company markets and sells its products through magazine advertising, trade shows and the internet.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company has a diverse customer base both domestically and abroad
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with international sales accounting for 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of total sales in 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and does not depend on one or a few customers for a material portion of its revenues.&nbsp; In 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, no one customer accounted for more than 10% of net sales.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Quality Control in Manufacturing
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In March&nbsp;1994,&nbsp;IKONICS became the first firm in northern Minnesota to receive ISO&nbsp;9001 certification.&nbsp; ISO 9000 is a worldwide standard issued by the International Organization for Standardization that provides a framework for quality assurance.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company has been recertified every three years beginning in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1997.&nbsp; IKONICS&#x2019; quality function goal is to train all employees properly in both their work and in the importance of their work.&nbsp; Internal records of quality, including related graphs and tables, are reviewed regularly and discussions are held among management and employees regarding how improvements might be realized.&nbsp; The Company has rigorous materials selection procedures and also uses testing procedures to assure its products meet quality standards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Research and Development and Intellectual Property
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company spent 3.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$66

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0
</FONT>

	,000
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on research and development in 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 3.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$6
</FONT>

	65
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in 201
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp; In its research program,&nbsp;IKONICS has developed ultraviolet light-sensitive chemistries used in the manufacture of screen print stencils, photoresists for abrasive etching and acid resist and prototyping ink jet fluids and ink jet receptive films.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company has a number of patents and patent applications on these chemistries and applications.&nbsp;&nbsp;There can be no assurance that any patent granted to the Company will provide adequate protection to the Company&#x2019;s intellectual property.&nbsp; Within the Company, steps are taken to protect the Company&#x2019;s trade secrets, including physical security, confidentiality and non-competition agreements with employees, non-disclosure agreements where applicable, and confidentiality agreements with vendors.&nbsp;&nbsp;Over the past few years, the Company has directed a larger portion of it research and development resources towards industrial inkjettable fluids and ink jet receptive substrates.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company has also invested significant resources for personnel and equipment to develop proprietary products and techniques for the etching of composite materials, industrial ceramics and electronic wafers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition to its patents, the Company has various trademarks including the &#x201C;IKONICS,&#x201D; &#x201C;Chromaline,&#x201D; &#x201C;IKONICS Imaging,&#x201D; &#x201C;Precision Abrasive Machining,&#x201D; &#x201C;SmartFlex,&#x201D; &#x201C;PhotoBrasive,&#x201D; &#x201C;AccuArt,&#x201D;&nbsp; &#x201C;Nichols,&#x201D; &#x201C;image mate,&#x201D; &#x201C;Alpha FlexTrace,&#x201D; &#x201C;Alpha MicroCap,&#x201D; and &#x201C;DTX&#x201D; trademarks.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Raw Materials
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The primary raw materials used by IKONICS in its production are photopolymers, polyester films, polyvinylacetates, polyvinylalcohols and water.&nbsp; The Company&#x2019;s purchasing staff leads in the identification of both domestic and foreign sources for raw materials and negotiates price and terms for all domestic and foreign markets.&nbsp; IKONICS&#x2019; involvement in foreign markets has given it the opportunity to become a global buyer of raw materials at lower overall cost.&nbsp; The Company has a number of suppliers for its operations.&nbsp; Some suppliers provide a significant amount of key raw materials to the Company, but the Company believes alternative sources are available for most materials.&nbsp; For those raw materials where an alternative source is not readily available, the Company has contingency raw material replacement plans.&nbsp; To date, there have been no significant shortages of raw materials.&nbsp; The Company believes it has good supplier relations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Competition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company competes in its markets based on product development capability, quality, reliability, availability, technical support and price.&nbsp; Though the screen printing market is much larger than the awards and recognition market,&nbsp;IKONICS commands significantly more market share in the latter.&nbsp;&nbsp;IKONICS has two primary
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	domestic
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	competitors in its screen printing film business.&nbsp; They are larger than IKONICS and possess greater resources than the Company in many areas.&nbsp; The Company has numerous competitors in the market for screen print emulsions, many of whom are larger than IKONICS and possess greater resources.&nbsp; The market for the Company&#x2019;s abrasive etching products in the awards and recognition market has one significant competitor.&nbsp; IKONICS considers itself to be the leader in this market.&nbsp; There are significant competitors, using different technologies in the new markets being entered by the Company. The primary competition for AMS is from other machining methods, most of which are well established. The primary competition for DTX comes from old, well-established technologies based on wax and screen printing and new competition from laser technologies.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company is subject to a variety of federal, state and local industrial laws and regulations, including those relating to the discharge of material into the environment and protection of the environment.&nbsp; The governmental authorities primarily responsible for regulating the Company&#x2019;s environmental compliance are the Environmental Protection Agency, the Minnesota Pollution Control Agency and the Western Lake Superior Sanitary District.&nbsp; Failure to comply with the laws promulgated by these authorities may result in monetary sanctions, liability for environmental
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>

The Company believes that it complies in all material respects with these regulations that apply to its current products.&nbsp; Failure to comply with these regulations could have a negative impact on the Company&#x2019;s operations and capital expenditures and such negative impact could be significant.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Item 1A.&nbsp; Risk Factors
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The Company&#x2019;s DTX and AMS initiatives involve new technologies that might not be executed successfully and might not achieve market acceptance, which would adversely affect the Company&#x2019;s results of operation, financial condition and prospects.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	DTX and AMS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	initiatives involve new technologies that might never achieve market acceptance.&nbsp;&nbsp;During 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, the Company generated operating losses in its AMS segment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and in 2014 its DTX segment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	realized an operating loss
</FONT>

	execution of these initiatives is important for its ability to grow its revenues and profits.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, if the Company fails to generate its projected revenues in these business units, the Company&#x2019;s investments in these areas would not generate the profits the Company expects and its results of operations, financial condition and prospects would be materially and adversely affected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Adverse changes to global economic conditions generally, and to the aerospace and automotive industries in particular, may harm the Company&#x2019;s business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The prospects for economic growth in the United States and other countries remain uncertain and major economies where the Company conducts business could continue or return to recessionary conditions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Economic concerns and issues such as reduced access to capital for businesses may cause the Company&#x2019;s customers to delay or reduce purchases of the Company&#x2019;s products.&nbsp;&nbsp;Given the continued uncertainty concerning the global economy, the Company also faces risks that may arise from financial difficulties experienced by suppliers and customers, such as an inability to collect receivables or the continued operation of suppliers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s AMS segment focuses primarily on customers in the aerospace industry, and its DTX segment focuses primarily on customers in the automotive industry.&nbsp;&nbsp;The aerospace and automotive industries have experienced volatility in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	prior
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years in a manner similar to or greater than the global economy generally.&nbsp;&nbsp;If either or both these industries experiences difficulties that reduce demand for their products generally, the Company&#x2019;s results of operations, financial condition and prospects would suffer.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The Company faces risks related to sales to government subcontractors, including potential delays or cancellations of planned sales and additional regulatory compliance costs and obligations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s customers for its AMS business unit manufacture aerospace products, and the Company derives a portion of its revenue as a subcontractor to general contractors working for the U.S. government.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a government subcontractor, demand and payment for the Company&#x2019;s products may be adversely affected by public sector budgetary cycles or funding authorizations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any cancellation or delay of product orders would adversely affect the Company&#x2019;s operating results and financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition, government subcontractors are subject to oversight, including special rules&nbsp;on accounting, expenses, reviews and security.&nbsp;&nbsp;This additional oversight could increase the Company&#x2019;s compliance costs and creates risk of a failure to comply with applicable rules&nbsp;and regulations.&nbsp;&nbsp;A failure to comply with these rules&nbsp;and regulations could result in termination of contracts, fines and suspensions, debarment from future government business or other penalties, any of which could adversely affect the Company&#x2019;s business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The Company faces significant competition and expects to face increasing competition in many aspects of its businesses, which could cause operating results to suffer.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company operates in highly competitive industries that experience rapid technological and market developments, changes in customer needs, and frequent product introductions and improvements, particularly with respect to the AMS and DTX businesses.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the Company is unable to anticipate and respond to these developments, its products or technologies could become uncompetitive or obsolete.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most of the Company&#x2019;s competitors in the AMS and DTX fields are larger and better capitalized than the Company with longer operating histories.&nbsp;&nbsp;These advantages could allow the Company&#x2019;s competitors to invest more in research and development and sales and marketing than the Company, which could make the competitive products more attractive or better known to consumers than the Company&#x2019;s products.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, because there is rapid technological change in fields in which the Company operates, the Company could face competition from new sources in the future that customers find more attractive.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company also could face increased competition in its traditional Domestic and IKONICS Imaging units.&nbsp;&nbsp;Capital costs for machinery necessary to operate in these industries have decreased in recent years, increasing the possibility that the Company will face new competitors.&nbsp;&nbsp;An increase in the amount of competition the Company faces, or a loss of competitiveness in any of the Company&#x2019;s business units for any reason, could adversely affect its revenues and gross margins.
</FONT>

<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	potentially adverse tax consequences, including the complexities of foreign value added tax systems and restrictions on the repatriation of earnings.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The occurrence of any one of these risks could negatively affect the Company&#x2019;s international business and, consequently, its results of operations generally.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The Company faces risks related to sales through distributors and other third parties.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	70
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of the Company&#x2019;s sales, including nearly all sales of its Domestic products and nearly all of its International sales, were conducted through third parties.&nbsp;&nbsp;Using third parties for distribution exposes the Company to many risks, including competitive pressure, concentration, credit risk and compliance risks.&nbsp;&nbsp;Distributors may sell products that compete with the Company&#x2019;s products, and the loss of a distributor could reduce the Company&#x2019;s revenue.&nbsp;&nbsp;Distributors may face financial difficulties, including bankruptcy, which could harm the Company&#x2019;s collection of accounts receivable and financial results.&nbsp;&nbsp;Violations of the FCPA or similar laws by distributors or other third-party intermediaries could have a material impact on the Company&#x2019;s business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Failing to manage risks related to the Company&#x2019;s use of distributors may reduce sales, increase expenses, and weaken its competitive position.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Increases in prices and declines in the availability of raw materials could negatively impact the Company&#x2019;s financial results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Certain raw materials needed to manufacture products are obtained from a limited number of suppliers and many of the raw materials are petroleum-based.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under normal market conditions, these raw materials are generally available on the open market from a variety of producers.&nbsp;&nbsp;While alternate supplies of most key raw materials are available, supplier production outages may lead to strained supply-demand situations for certain raw materials.&nbsp;&nbsp;The substitution of key raw materials could require the Company to identify new supply sources, or reformulate and retest products or processes.&nbsp;&nbsp;From time to time, the prices and availability of these raw materials may fluctuate, which could
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage9"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	impair the Company&#x2019;s ability to procure necessary materials, or increase the cost of manufacturing products.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the prices of raw materials increase in a short period of time, the Company may be unable to pass these increases on to its customers in a timely manner or at all, which could reduce its gross margins.&nbsp;&nbsp;Like most companies in the Company&#x2019;s industries, the Company does not have long-term supply contracts for most of its key raw materials, which exacerbates the foregoing risks to the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	If any of the Company&#x2019;s present single or limited source suppliers become unavailable or inadequate, its customer relationships, results of operations and financial condition may be adversely affected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company acquires certain of its materials that are critical to its operations from a limited number of third parties.&nbsp;&nbsp;Should any of the Company&#x2019;s current single or limited source suppliers become unavailable or inadequate, or impose terms unacceptable to the Company such as increased pricing terms, the Company could be required to spend a significant amount of time and expense to develop alternate sources of supply, and may not be successful in doing so on acceptable terms or at all.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the Company is unable to find a suitable supplier for a particular material, it could be required to modify its existing business processes or offerings to accommodate the situation.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, the loss of a single or limited source supplier could adversely affect the Company&#x2019;s relationship with its customers and its results of operations and financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The Company depends on one manufacturer to make and sell DTX printers. If the manufacturer ceased to make or sell DTX printers, or failed to meet quality standards, the Company&#x2019;s financial results and prospects would be adversely affected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company relies on one company to manufacture and sell DTX printers.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the manufacturer ceased to produce or devote resources to selling DTX printers, due to a change in company strategy, to focus on alternative initiatives, or for any other reason, the Company would need to find an alternative manufacturer and seller of DTX printers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Finding an alternative manufacturer and seller of DTX printers could result in additional costs and delays in growing the Company&#x2019;s DTX business unit, which would adversely affect the Company&#x2019;s financial results and prospects.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition, if these manufacturers failed to produce DTX printers that satisfy the Company&#x2019;s quality standards, the Company&#x2019;s reputation with end users could be harmed and the Company could be forced to find a new manufacturer.&nbsp;&nbsp;Either of these results also would harm the Company&#x2019;s business and prospects.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The inability to attract and retain qualified personnel could adversely impact the Company&#x2019;s business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Sustaining and growing the Company&#x2019;s business depends on the recruitment, development and retention of qualified employees, including management and research and development personnel.&nbsp;&nbsp;The inability to recruit and retain key personnel or the unexpected loss of key personnel may adversely affect the Company&#x2019;s operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	An active trading market for the Company&#x2019;s shares of common stock may not develop.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s common stock has been listed for trading on the Nasdaq Capital Market since 1999 and persistently has experienced limited trading volume.&nbsp;&nbsp;There can be no assurance that an active public market for the Company&#x2019;s shares will develop or be sustained.&nbsp;&nbsp;The lack of an active trading market could adversely affect the price and liquidity of the Company&#x2019;s common stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The Company&#x2019;s directors and officers own a large percentage of the Company&#x2019;s common stock, which may allow them to collectively exert significant influence over substantially all matters requiring shareholder approval.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As of December&nbsp;31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, the Company&#x2019;s directors and officers collectively beneficially owned approximately 33.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of its common stock outstanding as of that date.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, the Company&#x2019;s directors and officers could exert significant influence over all matters requiring a shareholder vote, including the election of directors, amendments to the Company&#x2019;s articles of incorporation, and extraordinary transactions such as mergers or going private transactions.&nbsp;&nbsp;These ownership positions may have the effect of delaying, deterring or preventing a change in control or a change in the composition of the Company&#x2019;s board of directors.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, substantial sales of shares beneficially owned by our directors or officers could be viewed negatively by third parties and have a negative impact on the Company&#x2019;s stock price.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition, stock markets in general have experienced price and volume fluctuations in recent years, fluctuations that sometimes have been unrelated to the operating performance of the affected companies.&nbsp;&nbsp;These broad market fluctuations may adversely affect the market price of the Company&#x2019;s common stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;The market price of the Company&#x2019;s common stock could decline below its current price and the market price of the Company&#x2019;s shares may fluctuate significantly in the future.&nbsp;&nbsp;These fluctuations may be unrelated to the Company&#x2019;s performance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The Company&#x2019;s operating results and financial condition may fluctuate on a quarterly and annual basis.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s operating results and financial condition may fluctuate from quarter to quarter and year to year, and could vary due to a number of factors, some of which are outside of the Company&#x2019;s control.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the Company&#x2019;s actual or projected operating results may fail to match its past performance.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s operating results and financial condition may fluctuate due to a number of factors, including those listed below and those identified throughout this &#x201C;Risk Factors&#x201D; section:
</FONT>

<EFX_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION>
<A NAME="FIS_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Item 7.&nbsp;&nbsp;Management&#x2019;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The following management discussion and analysis focuses on those factors that had a material effect on the Company&#x2019;s financial results of operations and financial condition during 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and should be read in connection with the Company&#x2019;s audited financial statements and notes thereto for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, included herein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Critical Accounting Policies and Estimates
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company prepares its financial statements in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America.&nbsp;&nbsp;Therefore, the Company is required to make certain estimates, judgments and assumptions that the Company believes are reasonable based upon the information available.&nbsp;&nbsp;These estimates and assumptions affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities at the date of the financial statements and the reported amounts of revenues and expenses during the periods presented.&nbsp;&nbsp;The accounting policies and estimates which IKONICS believes are the most critical to aid in fully understanding and evaluating its reported financial results include the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Trade Receivables.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company performs ongoing credit evaluations of its customers and adjusts credit limits based upon payment history and the customer&#x2019;s current credit worthiness, as determined by review of the current credit information.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company continuously monitors collections and payments from its customers and maintains a provision for estimated credit losses based upon historical experience and any specific customer collection issues that have been identified.&nbsp;&nbsp;While such credit losses have historically been within expectations and the provisions established, the Company cannot guarantee that it will continue to experience the same collection history that has occurred in the past.&nbsp;&nbsp;The general payment terms are net 30-45 days for domestic customers and net 30-90 days for foreign customers.&nbsp;&nbsp;A small percentage of the trade receivables balance is denominated in a foreign currency with no concentration in any given country.&nbsp;&nbsp;At the end of each reporting period, the Company analyzes the receivable balance for customers paying in a foreign currency.&nbsp;&nbsp;These balances are adjusted to each quarter or year-end spot rate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company also maintains a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage13"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	provision based upon historical experience and any specifically identified issues for any customer related returns, refunds or credits.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Inventories.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Inventories are valued at the lower of cost or market value using the last in, first out (LIFO) method.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company monitors its inventory for obsolescence and records reductions from cost when required.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Income Taxes.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Deferred taxes are provided on a liability method whereby deferred tax assets are recognized for deductible temporary differences and operating loss and tax credit carryforwards and deferred tax liabilities are recognized for taxable temporary differences.&nbsp;&nbsp;Temporary differences are the differences between the reported amounts of assets and liabilities and their tax bases.&nbsp;&nbsp;Deferred tax assets are reduced by a valuation allowance when, in the opinion of management, it is more likely than not that some portion or all of the deferred tax assets will not be realized.&nbsp;&nbsp;Deferred tax assets and liabilities are adjusted for the effects of changes in tax laws and rates on the date of enactment.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company follows the accounting standard on accounting for uncertainty in income taxes, which addresses the determination of whether tax benefits claimed or expected to be claimed on a tax return should be recorded in the financial statements.&nbsp; Under this guidance, the Company may recognize the tax benefit from an uncertain tax position only if it is more likely than not that the tax position will be sustained on examination by taxing authorities, based on the technical merits of the position.&nbsp; The tax benefits recognized in the financial statements from such a position are measured based on the largest benefit that has a greater than 50 percent likelihood of being realized upon ultimate settlement.&nbsp; The guidance on accounting for uncertainty in income taxes also addresses derecognition, classification, interest and penalties on income taxes, and accounting in interim periods.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue Recognition.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company recognizes revenue on sales of products when title passes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	which can occur at the time of shipment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or when the goods arrive at the customer location depending on the agreement with the customer.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company sells its products to both distributors and end-users.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sales to distributors and end-users are recorded based upon the criteria governed by the sales, delivery, and payment terms stated on the invoices from the Company to the purchaser.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to transfer of title / risk of loss, all revenue is recorded in accordance with the criteria outlined within SAB 104 and FASB ASC 605
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Revenue Recognition:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 108PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(a)&nbsp;persuasive evidence of an arrangement (principally in the form of customer sales orders and the Company&#x2019;s sales invoices)
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 108PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 108PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(b)&nbsp;delivery and performance (evidenced by proof of delivery, e.g. the shipment of film and substrates with bill of lading used for proof of delivery for FOB shipping point terms, and the carrier booking confirmation report used for FOB destination terms).&nbsp;&nbsp;Once the finished product is shipped and physically delivered under the terms of the invoice and sales order, the Company has no additional performance or service obligations to complete
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 108PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 108PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(c)&nbsp;a fixed and determinable sales price (the Company&#x2019;s pricing is established and is not based on variable terms, as evidenced in either the Company&#x2019;s invoices or the limited number of distribution agreements; the Company rarely grants extended payment terms and has no history of concessions)
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 108PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 108PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(d)&nbsp;a reasonable likelihood of payment (the Company&#x2019;s terms are standard, and the Company does not have a substantial history of customer defaults or non-payment)
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 108PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Sales are reported on a net basis by deducting credits, estimated normal returns and discounts.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s return policy does not vary by geography.&nbsp;&nbsp;The customer has no rotation or price protection rights and the Company is not under a warranty obligation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Freight billed to customers is included in sales.&nbsp;&nbsp;Shipping costs are included in cost of goods sold.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	resulted in a $239,000, or 3.0%, decrease in Domestic sales versus the same period in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;Partially offsetting these sales decreases was a $301,000, or 92% increase in AMS sales as the Company has begun to recei
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	Income Taxes.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During 2015, the Company realized income tax expense of $90,000, or an effective rate of 40.0%, compared to income tax expense of $270,000, or an effective rate of 29.4%, for the same period in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;The decrease in income tax expense from 2014 is primarily due to lower profitability in 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increase in the effective tax rate is mainly driven by a decrease in the domestic manufacturing deduction from lower profitability in 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	2015, and higher rate impact of non-deductible items resulting from significantly lower pre-tax book income in 2015

	also contributed the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	rate

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During 2015, inventories decreased by $511,000.&nbsp;&nbsp;The lower inventory
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	balance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	reflect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	efforts to tighten inventory
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	levels on hand
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	along with the timing of raw material purchases.&nbsp;&nbsp;Trade receivables increased $69,000 related to increased fourth quarter sales.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Accounts payable increased $49,000 due to the timing of payments to and purchases from vendors while accrued liabilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	creased $8,000.&nbsp;&nbsp;Income taxes receivables decreased $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	61
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,000 due to the timing of estimated 2015 tax payments compared to the calculated 2015 tax liability.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During 2014, inventories increased by $76,000.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to increased finished goods levels, part of the inventory increase is related to the timing of raw material purchases.&nbsp;&nbsp;Trade receivables increased $45,000 related to the increase in sales volumes.&nbsp;&nbsp;The $17,000 decrease in prepaid expenses and other assets is related to a decrease in prepaid promotional expenses.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accounts payable decreased $161,000 due to the timing of payments to and purchases from vendors while accrued liabilities increased $31,000 due to the timing of the Company&#x2019;s payroll.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s income tax receivable increased $122,000 due to timing of estimated 2014 tax payments compared to the calculated 2014 tax liability.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company markets its products in numerous countries in various regions of the world, including North America, Europe, Latin America, and Asia.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4.9

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	though
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a portion is transacted in Euros.&nbsp;&nbsp;IKONICS has not implemented an economic hedging strategy to reduce the risk of foreign currency translation exposures, which management does not believe to be significant based on the scope and geographic diversity of the Company&#x2019;s foreign operations as of December&nbsp;31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>

	5

</FONT>

	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Future Outlook
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	IKONICS has spent on average approximately 4% of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	annual
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales in research and development and has made capital expenditures related to its DTX and AMS programs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company plans to maintain its efforts in this area to expedite internal product development as well as to form technological alliances with outside experts to commercialize new product opportunities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company continues to make progress on its AMS business initiative.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company has entered into agreements with major aerospace companies a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	long with working on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	smaller
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	development
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	programs to determine the feasibility of using its unique technologies in the production of military and commercial aircraft.&nbsp;&nbsp;Progress is being made on a number of these in-house feasibility projects, and the Company believes that several of these could lead to ongoing business.&nbsp;&nbsp;In anticipation of this business, the Company is expanding its AMS capacity and patent applications.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company is also continuing to pursue DTX related business initiatives.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to making efforts towards growing the inkjet technology business, the Company offers a range of products for creating texture surfaces and has introduced a fluid for use in prototyping. The Company is currently working on production improvements to enhance its customer offerings.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company has been awarded European, Japanese and United States patents on its DTX technologies.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company has modified its DTX technology to enter the market for prototyping and 3D printing.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Domestically, both the Domestic and IKONICS Imaging units remain profitable in mature markets&nbsp;and require aggressive strategies to grow market share. Although there will be challenges, the Company believes these businesses will continue to grow and prosper.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to its traditional emphasis on domestic markets, the Company will continue efforts to grow its business internationally by attempting to develop new markets and expanding market share where it has already established a presence. However, the strong U.S. dollar made this challenging
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2015, and the Company anticipates continued strength of the U.S. dollar in the near term.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition to the $3.5 million building expansion to accommodate the AMS division and the implementation of a new ERP system, other future activities undertaken to expand the Company&#x2019;s business may include acquisitions, building improvements, equipment additions, new product development and marketing opportunities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage17"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Off-Balance Sheet Arrangements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company has no off-balance sheet arrangements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Recent Accounting Pronouncements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In May&nbsp;2014, the Financial Accounting Standards Board (&#x201C;FASB&#x201D;) issued Accounting Standards Update (&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ASU
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;) No.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2014-09
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue from Contracts with Customers.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ASU 2014-09
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;supersedes the revenue recognition requirements in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue Recognition (Topic 605
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	), and requires entities to recognize revenue in a way that depicts the transfer of promised goods or services to customers in an amount that reflects the consideration to which the entity expects to be entitled to in exchange for those goods or services.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In August 2015, the FASB issued ASU 2015-14,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue from Contracts with Customers: Deferral of the Effective Date,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	which defers the adoption of ASU 2014-09 to annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2017, including interim reporting periods within that reporting period. Earlier application is permitted only as of annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2016, including interim reporting periods within that reporting period.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp; The Company is currently evaluating the effect that adopting this new accounting guidance will have on its condensed statements of operations, cash flows and financial position.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In 2014, the FASB issued ASU No. 2014-15,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Presentation of Financial Statements&#x2014;Going Concern (Subtopic 205-40): Disclosure of Uncertainties about an Entity&#x2019;s Ability to Continue as a Going Concern
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, intended to define management&#x2019;s responsibility to evaluate whether there is substantial doubt about an organization&#x2019;s ability to continue as a going concern and to provide related footnote disclosures.&nbsp;&nbsp;ASU 2014-15 is effective for the Company in the year ended December 31, 2016, and interim periods beginning March 31, 2017, with early application permitted. The Company does not anticipate a material impact to the financial statements once implemented.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In 2015, the FASB issued ASU No. 2015-11,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Inventory (Topic 330)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Related to Simplifying the Measurement of Inventory which applies to all inventory except inventory that is measured using last-in, first-out (LIFO) or the retail inventory method.&nbsp;&nbsp;Inventory measured using first-in, first-out (FIFO) or average cost is covered by the new amendments.&nbsp;&nbsp;Inventory within the scope of the new guidance should be measured at the lower of cost and net realizable value.&nbsp;&nbsp;Net realizable value is the estimated selling prices in the ordinary course of business, less reasonably predictable costs of completion, disposal, and transportation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Subsequent measurement is unchanged for inventory measured using LIFO or the retail inventory method.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendments will take effect for public business entities for fiscal years beginning after December 15, 2016, including interim periods within those fiscal years. The new guidance should be applied prospectively, and earlier application is permitted as of the beginning of an interim or annual reporting period.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company does not anticipate the adoption of the standard to have a material impact on the financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In 2015, the FASB issued ASU No. 2015-17,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Income Taxes (Topic 740): Balance Sheet Classification of Deferred Taxes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, requiring that deferred tax assets and liabilities be classified as noncurrent in a classified balance sheet.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendment takes effect for public entities for fiscal years beginning after December 15, 2016, with early adoption available.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company plans to adopt ASU No. 2015-17 in the first quarter of 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company does not anticipate the adoption of the standard to have a material impact on the financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_LIQUIDITY_CAPITAL>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	To the Board of Directors and Stockholders
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	IKONICS Corporation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have audited the accompanying balance sheets of IKONICS Corporation as of December&nbsp;31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, and the related statements of income, stockholders&#x2019; equity, and cash flows for the years then ended.&nbsp;&nbsp;These financial statements are the responsibility of the Company&#x2019;s management.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our responsibility is to express an opinion on these financial statements based on our audits.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We conducted our audits in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States).&nbsp;&nbsp;Those standards require that we plan and perform the audit to obtain reasonable assurance about whether the financial statements are free of material misstatement.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company is not required to have, nor were we engaged to perform, an audit of its internal control over financial reporting.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our audits included consideration of internal control over financial reporting as a basis for designing audit procedures that are appropriate in the circumstances, but not for the purpose of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the Company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, we express no such opinion.&nbsp;&nbsp;An audit also includes examining, on a test basis, evidence supporting the amounts and disclosures in the financial statements, assessing the accounting principles used and significant estimates made by management, as well as evaluating the overall financial statement presentation.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that our audits provide a reasonable basis for our opinion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In our opinion, the financial statements referred to above present fairly, in all material respects, the financial position of IKONICS Corporation as of December&nbsp;31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, and the results of its operations and its cash flows for the years then ended, in conformity with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles.
</FONT>
</P>
